        <hl1>THE MARKETS: CURRENCIES</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Euro drops against US dollar after surprise decline in German business confidence; in New York, euro settles at 89.79 cents, down from 90.15 cents; graph; chart (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>EURO FALTERS. The euro dropped against the dollar after a surprise decline in German business confidence. In New York, the euro settled at 89.79 cents, down from 90.15 cents on Monday.</p>
      </block>
